{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eda35f4b-72d0-4f0c-915d-f3a7c0e3b2d3","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** — upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n\n2. **Remove** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference — it's VSTest-specific and no longer needed.\n\n3. **Add the MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable the entry point** — add:\n   ```xml\n   <ItemGroup>\n     <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n   </ItemGroup>\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as before — it now routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.\n\n> **Note:** Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options or custom adapters may need adjusting. Review your test run settings if you have any.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3c8c06d6-b384-4497-a261-317877eacee7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":365},"id":"fe34fab4-9a44-4a7d-afbc-2f46ff844e94","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:42:55.115Z","parentId":"fb5ae546-be0e-4c91-8d5a-dfd7c5d59e7f"}
